<section class="row content justify-content-center">
  <div class="col-md-8">
    <h2>Add new user league</h2>
    <p>Complete the form to request a new user league. You must include a name and description. The request must be approved by an administrator before it will be visible. Once the league has been created, you will be set as the organiser.</p>
    <p>If you set the league to be public, any player can join the league.</p>
    <p>The default setting is private which means you, as the administrator, will need to manage any requests to join the league. You will see a list of all requests on both the league page and the options on your home page.</p>
    <form action="/leagues/add" id="leagueAdd" method="post">
      <fieldset class="form-group">
        <label for="name">Name:</label>
        <input placeholder="(required) e.g. my new league" class="form-control" type="text" id="name" name="name" />
        <label for="desc">Description:</label>
        <textarea rows="8" placeholder="(required) emoji (:football:) and _markdown_ are both supported" class="form-control" name="desc" id="desc"></textarea>
        <label for="public">Public:</label>
        <input class="form-control-inline" type="checkbox" name="public" id="public" />
        <input type="submit" class="form-control btn btn-primary" value="submit" />      
      </fieldset>
    </form>
    <aside>
      <p>You can use markdown and include emoji in the league description.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><i>_italics_</i></li>
        <li><strong>**bold**</strong></li>
        <li><a href="https://google.com">[link](https://google.com)</a></li>
        <li><a target="_blank" href="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/omnidan/node-emoji/master/lib/emoji.json">list</a> of emoji</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</section>
